rComments: Cahill is my absolute fav. His enthusiasm is so infectious that even seemingly dry material becomes fun. Once he got angry at the class because almost no one had done the reading, but he is such a positive sweetheart that it still came out positive. Has high expectation but does his best to allow you to be successful if you get his help.

Also had him for INI215 and FCS310. Cahill is my favourite prof hands down. Dorky and aware of it, challenges issues like sexism/racism/heterocentrism in course materials, only makes you read what is necessary, clearly explains course material and so so so knowledgeable and passionate.
Completely impossible to understand. Jumps all over the place making what appear to the students to be tenuous connections between the readings and their supposed application to film.

One of the best, though toughest, professors at Innis. I say that with utmost respect; he pushes his students to truly realize their potential, though that first C  or B- may sting a bit, it's absolutely worth it in the long run when you finally get your A-- and know you've truly earned it. Prof Cahill clearly has a great passion for cinema studies and I couldn't ask for a better person to teach the class. He is always excited to teach his class and always makes quirky jokes that make the class just that much better! If he is ever teaching a course, TAKE IT!!

Prof Cahill is knowledgeable and engaging. He is a little goofy but that adds to his 'charm'. He is conscientious of the fact that not everyone comes from film background and explains concepts well. He is open-minded and appreciates every feedback and participation from his students. Also he leaves great feedback for essays, which I appreciated.

Prof. Cahill was fantastic in both the courses I took with him (the other being film cultures). He speaks clearly and concisely so he's very good for taking notes. He doesn't ramble off on tangents like some professors and he is clearly interested in his work. He is friendly, smart and energetic. I highly recommend him!
